    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - REASSEMBLY - SPINDLE YOKE ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SPINDLE YOKE ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack the roller bearing with lubricant and press into place in the spindle yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201037">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201037" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/g0201037.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Installing Roller Bearing in Spindle Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the outside circumference of the outer drive yoke seal with Loctite Sleeve N' Bearing
                Mount #609 (green). Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_25.xml" xrefid="f0201030">Figure 30</hotlnk>. Press the seal into place in the
                spindle yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0201038">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0201038" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/g0201038.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Installing Outer Drive Yoke Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rest the spindle yoke with its inboard side down. Install the lower kingpin mounting
                studs.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
